WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Storylines, Level 1.

00:09.000 --> 00:12.000
The Watchers by Jennifer Bassett.

00:18.000 --> 00:21.000
1. The big caves.

00:21.000 --> 00:25.000
Storylines, Level 2. The big caves.

00:52.000 --> 00:55.000
Are we dead or alive?

00:55.000 --> 00:57.000
It is not important.

00:57.000 --> 01:01.000
We sit and we wait and we watch.

01:01.000 --> 01:04.000
For 3,000 years.

01:04.000 --> 01:08.000
We are the Watchers.

01:08.000 --> 01:10.000
The guard is here too.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
The guard to Poseidon.

01:12.000 --> 01:15.000
The guard of the sea stands here in this fall.

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
We watch his statue.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
It is gold.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
All gold.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
He stands here 5 meters tall.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
His arms are gold.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
His hair is gold.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
His face is gold.

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
And his gold eyes shine.

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
His dark fall.

01:35.000 --> 01:38.000
We are the Watchers.

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
Jim and Stella, his sister, are on holiday in Greece.

01:42.000 --> 01:46.000
They are staying at a hotel in Iraqlion, on Crete.

01:46.000 --> 01:49.000
They are talking to their friend, Nikos.

01:49.000 --> 01:54.000
Nikos is a Cretean and lives near the Palace of Knosses.

02:02.000 --> 02:04.000
What are we going to do tomorrow?

02:04.000 --> 02:06.000
Can we go to Knosses?

02:06.000 --> 02:07.000
Yes.

02:07.000 --> 02:08.000
Why not?

02:08.000 --> 02:10.000
It is a very famous place.

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
And very, very old.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.000
About 3,000 or 4,000 years old.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
Yes, I would like to.

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
Stella, look at this.

02:19.000 --> 02:20.000
It is about Knosses.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
It is very interesting.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
Caves under Knosses.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
Iraqlion, Crete.

02:26.000 --> 02:30.000
Under the famous Palace of Knosses, there are many caves.

02:30.000 --> 02:33.000
Some of these caves are very big.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
There are many, many meters under the ground.

02:36.000 --> 02:38.000
What is in these caves?

02:38.000 --> 02:39.000
Nobody knows.

02:39.000 --> 02:42.000
The caves are very dangerous.

02:42.000 --> 02:46.000
Next week, Janis Padakis is going to...

02:46.000 --> 02:49.000
We are going to find these caves, Stella.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Are you coming with us, Nikos?

02:51.000 --> 02:52.000
But Jim?

02:52.000 --> 02:53.000
Yes, yes.

02:53.000 --> 02:54.000
I am coming with you.

02:54.000 --> 02:58.000
You can stay with me at my mother's house near Knosses.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.000
Good.

02:59.000 --> 03:01.000
We are going to need a lot of things.

03:01.000 --> 03:04.000
We are going to find the caves under Knosses.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
Yes, but it is OK.

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
I can get everything.

03:08.000 --> 03:11.000
Jim, the caves are dangerous.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.000
Yes, but Nikos knows a lot about caves.

03:14.000 --> 03:15.000
Yes, I do.

03:15.000 --> 03:18.000
And I know the Palace of Knosses very well.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
Don't forget, I won't there.

03:20.000 --> 03:23.000
But do you know these caves under Knosses?

03:23.000 --> 03:25.000
No, I don't.

03:25.000 --> 03:27.000
But we are going to be careful.

03:27.000 --> 03:28.000
Oh, all right.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.000
When are we going?

03:30.000 --> 03:37.000
Tomorrow.

03:37.000 --> 03:41.000
Sometimes the Relights in these halls are music.

03:41.000 --> 03:44.000
The people from the Palace come down here.

03:44.000 --> 03:48.000
They are small, quick people with dark eyes and dark hair.

03:48.000 --> 03:52.000
They bring lights and food and water.

03:52.000 --> 03:55.000
And they dance the dance of the God.

03:55.000 --> 03:58.000
They are the Gods people.

03:59.000 --> 04:02.000
No, no, I forget.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
They do not come now.

04:04.000 --> 04:09.000
These halls are quiet, dark and quiet.

04:09.000 --> 04:11.000
It is always night now.

04:11.000 --> 04:15.000
There is no music, no dancing.

04:15.000 --> 04:18.000
There are no people in the Palace now.

04:18.000 --> 04:21.000
Not after the fire and the water from the sea.

04:21.000 --> 04:25.000
They are dead, all dead.

04:25.000 --> 04:29.000
And we, the Ketter and I, sit in the hall of the God.

04:29.000 --> 04:32.000
We wait and we watch.

04:32.000 --> 04:36.000
We are the Gods watches.

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
Two.

04:46.000 --> 04:48.000
The first day.

04:48.000 --> 04:50.000
At the Palace of Knosses.

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
It is seven o'clock in the morning.

04:53.000 --> 04:56.000
Knickers is looking for the door to the caves.

04:56.000 --> 04:59.000
Jim and Stella are waiting for him.

04:59.000 --> 05:02.000
The sun is hot.

05:02.000 --> 05:05.000
I'm thirsty. I'm going to drink some water.

05:05.000 --> 05:08.000
Don't drink a lot. We need it in the caves.

05:08.000 --> 05:10.000
Have we got everything?

05:10.000 --> 05:13.000
I think so. The bags are very heavy.

05:13.000 --> 05:16.000
Jim, Stella, the door is here.

05:16.000 --> 05:19.000
Come on. We can go down now.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Be careful.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
It's very dark.

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
I can't see anything.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
Here. Hold this light.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
We need all the lights now.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.000
Walk slowly and be very careful.

05:37.000 --> 05:40.000
Yes, I know.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
How many caves are there?

05:43.000 --> 05:45.000
This is the 10th cave now.

05:45.000 --> 05:48.000
I can see another one in front of us.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
A long one.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.000
I'm tired.

05:53.000 --> 05:56.000
I don't want to look at any more caves today.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.000
How about some food? I'm hungry.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
Yes. Let's eat something.

06:01.000 --> 06:03.000
And we can stay here for the night.

06:03.000 --> 06:07.000
Good. Where's the bag? The food is in there.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
How old are these caves, Nikos?

06:09.000 --> 06:11.000
I don't know.

06:11.000 --> 06:14.000
3,000 years? 4,000 years?

06:14.000 --> 06:17.000
Do many people come to these caves?

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
Not many people know.

06:20.000 --> 06:23.000
Only the old Greek gods.

06:23.000 --> 06:26.000
The god Poseidon lives in caves.

06:26.000 --> 06:29.000
Some people say that God Poseidon.

06:29.000 --> 06:31.000
There are no old gods in these caves.

06:31.000 --> 06:33.000
How do you know, Jim?

06:33.000 --> 06:36.000
The old Greek gods are only stories.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
We read about them in books.

06:38.000 --> 06:40.000
They're not important today.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.000
Oh, yes, they are.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.000
Don't laugh at them.

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
And Poseidon is a dangerous god.

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
All the books say that.

06:47.000 --> 06:49.000
He's the god of the sea.

06:49.000 --> 06:51.000
And the god of earthquakes too.

06:51.000 --> 06:54.000
We have a lot of earthquakes in Greece.

06:54.000 --> 06:55.000
Don't forget that.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
Oh, Nikos.

06:57.000 --> 06:58.000
That's silly.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
The god of earthquakes.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
Everybody knows the earthquakes.

07:02.000 --> 07:03.000
No, Jim.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.000
Nikos is right.

07:05.000 --> 07:07.000
We don't understand everything.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
And don't laugh at Poseidon.

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
Not here in these caves.

07:15.000 --> 07:19.000
The years come and the years go.

07:19.000 --> 07:22.000
3,000 years.

07:22.000 --> 07:26.000
My sister, Aketa, and I sit and wait.

07:26.000 --> 07:30.000
It is dark and cold in the hall of the god.

07:30.000 --> 07:33.000
The sun never shines here.

07:33.000 --> 07:36.000
Sometimes people come to these halls.

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
They are not the god's people.

07:38.000 --> 07:40.000
They look for gold.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.000
Only gold.

07:42.000 --> 07:44.000
And Poseidon is angry.

07:44.000 --> 07:47.000
It is the gold of his people.

07:47.000 --> 07:52.000
And now it is the god's gold because his people are dead.

07:52.000 --> 07:59.000
Nobody can take the god's gold or look at the gold face of the god and live.

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
But there are no lights.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.000
No people now.

08:03.000 --> 08:07.000
Only the god Poseidon stands here in this dark hall.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.000
God of the blue sea.

08:09.000 --> 08:11.000
God of the green sea.

08:11.000 --> 08:14.000
God of this dark hall.

08:14.000 --> 08:19.000
We are his watchers.

08:20.000 --> 08:46.000
3, the second day.

08:46.000 --> 08:48.000
Wake up, Stella.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
Good morning, Nickos.

08:50.000 --> 08:51.000
Morning.

08:51.000 --> 08:53.000
It is always night in these caves.

08:53.000 --> 08:55.000
What is the time?

08:55.000 --> 08:56.000
7 o'clock.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
Are we going on or back?

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
What do you think, Nickos?

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
I don't know.

09:02.000 --> 09:04.000
How many caves are there?

09:04.000 --> 09:06.000
15, 20?

09:06.000 --> 09:07.000
I don't know.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.000
But we can look at the next one.

09:09.000 --> 09:10.000
Or two.

09:10.000 --> 09:13.000
Or three, or four, or five.

09:13.000 --> 09:14.000
I know you, Jim.

09:14.000 --> 09:16.000
You want to see everything.

09:17.000 --> 09:20.000
This is the 14th cave.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
And this cave is big.

09:22.000 --> 09:23.000
Very big.

09:23.000 --> 09:24.000
Look.

09:24.000 --> 09:26.000
This is a road.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
We're walking on a road.

09:28.000 --> 09:29.000
Yes.

09:29.000 --> 09:30.000
You're right.

09:30.000 --> 09:32.000
It's a very old road too.

09:32.000 --> 09:35.000
Look at these stones on the floor.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
Thousands of years old.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
But whose road is it?

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
And where does it go to?

09:41.000 --> 09:42.000
I don't know.

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
But we can follow it.

09:44.000 --> 09:46.000
But it's six o'clock now.

09:46.000 --> 09:48.000
I think...

09:48.000 --> 09:49.000
Listen.

09:49.000 --> 09:50.000
I can hear water.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.000
Can you hear it?

09:52.000 --> 09:54.000
There's a river in front of us.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.000
We can't get across a river.

09:56.000 --> 09:58.000
Oh, yes, we can.

09:58.000 --> 10:00.000
I don't want to go across.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.000
It's dangerous.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.000
No, it isn't.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
Come on, Stella.

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
Stella's right.

10:06.000 --> 10:08.000
Rivers under the ground are dangerous.

10:08.000 --> 10:10.000
Listen.

10:10.000 --> 10:12.000
I can hear something.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
It's only the river, Stella.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
It's all right.

10:16.000 --> 10:18.000
We can go across the river.

10:18.000 --> 10:21.000
And then we can stop and stay there for the night.

10:21.000 --> 10:22.000
Yes.

10:22.000 --> 10:25.000
We can make a fire and have some food.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.000
Listen, Sister.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.000
Do you hear anything?

10:35.000 --> 10:37.000
There are people at the river.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
They are talking and laughing.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
Listen, Sister.

10:41.000 --> 10:45.000
They are coming here to the hall of the God.

10:45.000 --> 10:47.000
Why?

10:47.000 --> 10:49.000
Who are they?

10:49.000 --> 10:51.000
What do they want?

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
Gold.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.000
They want gold.

10:55.000 --> 10:57.000
All people want gold.

10:57.000 --> 10:59.000
They cannot eat it.

10:59.000 --> 11:01.000
They cannot drink it.

11:01.000 --> 11:06.000
But the love of gold is in all men and women too.

11:07.000 --> 11:10.000
But they cannot take the God's gold.

11:10.000 --> 11:12.000
We are His watchers.

11:12.000 --> 11:16.000
We call the God and we say His name.

11:16.000 --> 11:21.000
Then the God wakes and His speaks.

11:31.000 --> 11:32.000
Gold.

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
The third day.

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
When are we going to go back?

11:40.000 --> 11:42.000
This is the third day now.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.000
I don't like these caves.

11:44.000 --> 11:46.000
Why not, Stella?

11:46.000 --> 11:48.000
I don't know.

11:48.000 --> 11:50.000
I can hear something.

11:50.000 --> 11:52.000
Or someone.

11:52.000 --> 11:54.000
It's not the river.

11:54.000 --> 11:56.000
I want to go back, Nikos.

11:56.000 --> 11:57.000
Yes.

11:57.000 --> 12:00.000
Sometimes I can hear something too.

12:00.000 --> 12:03.000
But there's nobody in these caves, Stella.

12:03.000 --> 12:04.000
Only us.

12:05.000 --> 12:07.000
Let's look at one more cave.

12:07.000 --> 12:09.000
Then we can go back.

12:09.000 --> 12:10.000
Okay?

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
What's Jim doing?

12:12.000 --> 12:13.000
I don't know.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.000
He's looking at something.

12:15.000 --> 12:17.000
Jim, what are you...

12:17.000 --> 12:18.000
Hey, look at this.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.000
It's a bowl.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.000
A gold bowl.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
It's beautiful.

12:23.000 --> 12:25.000
Can I hold it for a minute?

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
It's very heavy too.

12:27.000 --> 12:29.000
Look at all this gold.

12:29.000 --> 12:30.000
Is it old, Nikos?

12:30.000 --> 12:31.000
Yes.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.000
Thousands of years old, I think.

12:33.000 --> 12:35.000
We can sell it.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.000
We can get a lot of money for this bowl.

12:37.000 --> 12:38.000
We can't do that.

12:38.000 --> 12:39.000
It's not ours.

12:39.000 --> 12:40.000
Who's is it, then?

12:40.000 --> 12:42.000
It's, well, it's...

12:42.000 --> 12:44.000
I don't know.

12:44.000 --> 12:45.000
But it's not ours.

12:45.000 --> 12:47.000
Don't take it, Jim.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.000
Leave it here.

12:48.000 --> 12:49.000
No.

12:49.000 --> 12:50.000
I'm going to take it.

12:50.000 --> 12:52.000
It's ours now.

12:52.000 --> 12:54.000
Can you hear them, sister?

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
They are near the hall now.

12:56.000 --> 12:58.000
Listen.

12:58.000 --> 13:01.000
They are looking for gold.

13:01.000 --> 13:02.000
Gold.

13:02.000 --> 13:05.000
All people want gold.

13:09.000 --> 13:11.000
Look at that next cave.

13:11.000 --> 13:12.000
Can you see it?

13:12.000 --> 13:14.000
It's huge.

13:14.000 --> 13:15.000
It's not a cave.

13:15.000 --> 13:16.000
It's a...

13:16.000 --> 13:17.000
A hole.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.000
A huge hole.

13:18.000 --> 13:20.000
Jim, Nikos, don't go in there.

13:20.000 --> 13:22.000
Why not, Stella?

13:22.000 --> 13:24.000
I think someone is watching us.

13:24.000 --> 13:26.000
I don't like it.

13:26.000 --> 13:29.000
Why don't we go back, please?

13:29.000 --> 13:31.000
Who is watching us?

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
We're the only people here.

13:33.000 --> 13:34.000
I don't know.

13:34.000 --> 13:38.000
But someone or something is watching us.

13:38.000 --> 13:39.000
And it doesn't like us.

13:39.000 --> 13:41.000
Don't be silly, Stella.

13:41.000 --> 13:43.000
Nothing is watching us.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.000
Come on.

13:47.000 --> 13:50.000
I can see them now, sister.

13:50.000 --> 13:52.000
Two men and a woman.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.000
They are young.

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
Two of them have blue eyes.

13:56.000 --> 13:58.000
They are not people from the palace.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.000
They are not the gods, people.

14:03.000 --> 14:05.000
And they cannot come in here.

14:05.000 --> 14:08.000
They cannot take the gods gold.

14:08.000 --> 14:13.000
They cannot look at the face of the god.

14:17.000 --> 14:19.000
Look at those statues there.

14:19.000 --> 14:21.000
They're very, very old.

14:21.000 --> 14:23.000
I don't like them.

14:23.000 --> 14:25.000
Look at their eyes.

14:25.000 --> 14:27.000
Come away, Stella.

14:28.000 --> 14:30.000
I can see something at the end of the whole.

14:30.000 --> 14:31.000
Look.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.000
What is it?

14:32.000 --> 14:34.000
It's tall.

14:34.000 --> 14:36.000
Very tall.

14:36.000 --> 14:39.000
It's a statue, a huge statue.

14:39.000 --> 14:41.000
And it's shining.

14:41.000 --> 14:43.000
It's gold.

14:43.000 --> 14:45.000
Oh, gold.

14:45.000 --> 14:47.000
Don't look at it.

14:47.000 --> 14:48.000
Don't go in there.

14:48.000 --> 14:49.000
Please, Jim.

14:49.000 --> 14:50.000
Please.

14:50.000 --> 14:51.000
It's dangerous.

14:51.000 --> 14:52.000
Stop him, Nick.

14:52.000 --> 14:54.000
Stop him.

14:54.000 --> 14:57.000
They are looking into the whole now.

14:57.000 --> 14:59.000
Call the god.

14:59.000 --> 15:01.000
Now, sister.

15:01.000 --> 15:02.000
Now.

15:02.000 --> 15:05.000
Say the name of the god.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.000
They cannot come in.

15:07.000 --> 15:10.000
They cannot come in.

15:13.000 --> 15:14.000
Be quiet for a minute.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
Wait, Jim.

15:16.000 --> 15:17.000
Listen.

15:17.000 --> 15:18.000
Why?

15:18.000 --> 15:19.000
What's...

15:19.000 --> 15:21.000
I think Stella's right.

15:21.000 --> 15:22.000
There's something...

15:22.000 --> 15:23.000
Listen.

15:23.000 --> 15:24.000
Because...

15:24.000 --> 15:26.000
What's that?

15:26.000 --> 15:27.000
Can you hear it?

15:27.000 --> 15:28.000
Oh, no.

15:28.000 --> 15:29.000
No.

15:29.000 --> 15:30.000
The ground is moving.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
It's an earthquake.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
There's going to be an earthquake.

15:34.000 --> 15:35.000
The stones are falling.

15:35.000 --> 15:36.000
Run.

15:36.000 --> 15:37.000
Run.

15:37.000 --> 15:38.000
Back to the river.

15:38.000 --> 15:39.000
Run.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.000
Quick, Stella.

15:40.000 --> 15:41.000
Run.

15:41.000 --> 15:42.000
Run.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.000
We can't.

15:43.000 --> 15:45.000
The walls are falling.

15:45.000 --> 15:46.000
Everything is falling.

15:46.000 --> 15:48.000
We can't get out.

15:48.000 --> 15:50.000
We can't get out.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.000
Creek News.

15:59.000 --> 16:01.000
14th of August.

16:01.000 --> 16:04.000
Earthquake at Knosses.

16:04.000 --> 16:07.000
Three young people are dead.

16:07.000 --> 16:10.000
Erachlion Creek.

16:10.000 --> 16:15.000
Anna Stavros, mother of Nicos Stavros, says.

